snippet.textDisplay:
I was told to work from home for a week, for the first 3 days, I was in PJ, which did not affect my productivities, but on the 4th day, I thought I'd better get changed, just because...
But there were few issues that made some of my body parts not happy 😐:
(1) my home does not have a proper chair to fit the height of our desk, which was left in our guest room, and I can't sit on my bed with my laptop for too long, so my lower back is not happy :(
(2) when I am in the office, I need to go get printouts from the printer, to my manager's room, to meetings, to warehouse. At home, I don't need to go anywhere but sit on the chair, staring at my laptop to communicate with my colleagues, manager, meetings, handling my work within my office hours (exclude lunch time), so my bottom and feet (and the chair that I have sat on for 7.5 hours daily) are not happy :(
Well, I promise myself, when I need to work from home again, I must find another location to situation myself comfortablely... may be the sofa with a little fold-up table 🙃
I do feel blessed that I can still go to shops for essentials 😊
